    "{\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"# Code-Mixed Text Classifier\\n\",\"**NLP Project 64 of 100** — Handle Hinglish, Spanglish, and other code-mixed text for classification.\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"import numpy as np, pandas as pd, matplotlib.pyplot as plt, seaborn as sns\\nfrom sklearn.feature_extraction.text import TfidfVectorizer\\nfrom sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression\\nfrom sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score, classification_report\\nfrom sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\\nimport warnings; warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\\nsns.set_style('whitegrid')\\n%matplotlib inline\\nSEED = 42; rng = np.random.default_rng(SEED)\\nprint('Loaded.')\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"# Synthetic code-mixed data (Hinglish examples)\\nsamples = [\\n    ('yeh movie bahut acchi hai, must watch!','positive'),\\n    ('kya bakwas movie hai, time waste','negative'),\\n    ('amazing performance by the actors, bohot maza aaya','positive'),\\n    ('worst film ever, paisa barbaad','negative'),\\n    ('bahut funny hai, laughing nonstop','positive'),\\n    ('boring movie, fell asleep halfway','negative'),\\n    ('director ne kamaal kar diya, brilliant work','positive'),\\n    ('acting was terrible, bekaar movie','negative'),\\n    ('loved it so much, ek aur baar dekhungi','positive'),\\n    ('waste of time and money, avoid karo','negative'),\\n] * 30\\n\\ndf = pd.DataFrame(samples, columns=['text','sentiment'])\\ndf = df.sample(frac=1, random_state=SEED).reset_index(drop=True)\\nprint(f'Shape: {df.shape}'); print(df['sentiment'].value_counts())\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"code\",\"execution_count\":null,\"metadata\":{},\"outputs\":[],\"source\":[\"X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(df['text'], df['sentiment'], test_size=0.2, random_state=SEED)\\n\\n# Character n-grams work better for code-mixed text\\ntfidf = TfidfVectorizer(analyzer='char_wb', ngram_range=(3,5), max_features=5000)\\nX_tr = tfidf.fit_transform(X_train); X_te = tfidf.transform(X_test)\\n\\nlr = LogisticRegression(max_iter=500, random_state=SEED)\\nlr.fit(X_tr, y_train)\\ny_pred = lr.predict(X_te)\\n\\nprint(f'Accuracy: {accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred):.4f}')\\nprint(classification_report(y_test, y_pred))\"]},\n",
    "  {\"cell_type\":\"markdown\",\"metadata\":{},\"source\":[\"## Summary\\n\",\"- **Character n-grams work better** than word-level features for code-mixed text.\\n\",\"- **Code-mixed text breaks language-specific NLP tools** designed for one language.\\n\",\"- **Multilingual transformers (XLM-RoBERTa)** are the best production approach.\\n\",\"- **For production, combine language detection** with code-mixed-aware classifiers.\"]}\n",
    " ],\n",
